leaving right now

26:52.611 --> 26:54.195
while he still can.

26:59.868 --> 27:01.744
You're out there, man.

27:02.538 --> 27:05.039
All right.
One for the road.

27:07.835 --> 27:09.669
l'm headed back
to the Mountain

27:09.753 --> 27:14.257
to try to convince those old cowards
to stand up against the Vampaneze.

27:14.341 --> 27:19.095
Gavner, if we kill one
of them, it means war.

27:20.889 --> 27:22.890
Wouldn't that
be a shame?

27:27.313 --> 27:28.938
Poor old Vincent.

27:30.566 --> 27:33.234
You've been awfully
quiet under there.

27:56.592 --> 27:57.800
Get in.

28:20.366 --> 28:24.285
Thanks. Thanks,
l really needed a ride.

28:24.828 --> 28:27.622
Oh, absolutely,
absolutely delighted.

28:31.210 --> 28:33.503
Are you the one
known as Steve?

28:35.130 --> 28:39.425
No, l'm the one
known as Darren.

28:39.510 --> 28:41.844
l actually had a bike.

28:41.929 --> 28:45.348
But l'll just get it
tomorrow in the daylight.

28:45.891 --> 28:48.976
No need.
lt's in the trunk.

28:49.561 --> 28:53.398
Now, if l
may ask, Darren,

28:54.608 --> 28:59.654
do you believe in the
immutability of the human soul?

29:01.657 --> 29:02.865
The what?

29:02.950 --> 29:06.077
So, he knows nothing
of souls, does he?

29:06.995 --> 29:09.622
Knows only
of blood, huh?

29:09.706 --> 29:13.876
The pulsing, the
delicious, the ruby red.

29:21.009 --> 29:24.971
Wow, wow, you know what? You
can just let me off right here.

29:25.431 --> 29:27.098
What's the rush?

29:27.182 --> 29:31.894
After all, didn't we save you
from the scary, scary vampire?

29:34.982 --> 29:38.776
Doesn't act like
leadership material.

29:38.861 --> 29:42.363
Acts more like a bag
of blood. Are you? Huh?

29:42.531 --> 29:43.656
Bag of blood?

29:43.740 --> 29:46.033
Shows how much
you know, Murlaugh.

29:46.118 --> 29:48.744
l think he reeks
of potential.

29:49.538 --> 29:51.289
Ow!
Sorry.

29:52.791 --> 29:54.041
Souvenir.

30:00.090 --> 30:03.301
We all have
a destiny, Darren.

30:03.385 --> 30:07.096
And with a few simple tests,
we can find out what yours is.

30:09.391 --> 30:11.601
Wonderful to
meet you, Darren.

30:12.394 --> 30:15.354
lt's like looking
in a mirror.

30:26.283 --> 30:27.492
Darren!

30:28.535 --> 30:30.203
We'll be in touch.

30:50.182 --> 30:53.100
Freaky dream.
Freaky. Freaky.

30:59.483 --> 31:02.568
Hey. Hey, l'm gonna try
to get you some food, okay?

31:02.653 --> 31:06.489
Just hold on one sec. l'm gonna go get
some flies from the window sill, okay?

31:06.573 --> 31:09.242
Hey. Why have you
been acting so weird?

31:11.453 --> 31:12.703
l'm not acting weird.

31:12.788 --> 31:13.746
You were just talking
to your backpack.

31:13.830 --> 31:14.872
What?

31:14.957 --> 31:16.707
No, l wasn't.
Darren, yes, you were.

31:16.792 --> 31:18.459
l wasn't. Let me... Just
let me see it a second.

31:18.585 --> 31:20.294
You see? lt's just my
backpack. Seriously, stop it.

31:20.420 --> 31:22.672
Hey, give me my backpack,
man. Hey, just let me see it.

31:25.175 --> 31:27.218
Holy shit! That's...
That's the...

31:27.302 --> 31:30.680
Yeah, l went back to the theater after
the show and l kind of borrowed it.

31:30.806 --> 31:33.599
You stole from a vampire? Do
you realize you're a dead man?

31:33.684 --> 31:34.934
Shh!
You're a dead man!

31:35.018 --> 31:36.394
He's never gonna find me.

31:36.478 --> 31:37.937
Okay, just...

31:38.772 --> 31:42.567
Wait a second. When did you
go to Vur Horsten's room,

31:42.651 --> 31:44.485
and what did you see?

31:47.823 --> 31:49.574
All right,
l saw everything.

31:49.658 --> 31:52.326
Steve, are you crazy? Why would
you want to become a vampire?

31:52.411 --> 31:56.289
Listen, you can't understand.
You have everything.

31:57.165 --> 32:00.167
What do l have?
A secret best friend?

32:04.715 --> 32:05.965
Hey, leave it
in there, okay?

32:06.049 --> 32:07.425
lt's fine.
l want to see it.

32:07.509 --> 32:13.097
Be careful. Hey, be careful,
okay? Be really careful.

32:16.685 --> 32:19.604
This thing's even
more hideous close up.

32:19.688 --> 32:20.730
Can you just put it
back now, please?

32:35.662 --> 32:37.538
Okay,
l need the pipe.

32:39.082 --> 32:41.208
GlRL: l got a B-minus
in history.

32:42.210 --> 32:43.210
No!

32:46.381 --> 32:48.132
Oh, my gosh,
what is that?

33:01.897 --> 33:03.022
Move!

33:03.106 --> 33:04.231
Steve! Wait!

33:04.983 --> 33:06.400
What's going on?

33:19.122 --> 33:21.540
Move! Get out of
the way, idiots!

33:23.752 --> 33:26.837
Watch out! Move!

33:27.964 --> 33:29.632
Hey! Steve, don't!

33:32.010 --> 33:34.512
Now l got you!
Hold still!

33:35.722 --> 33:38.933
What's the matter with you?
Whose side are you on?

33:45.399 --> 33:47.858
Hey! No! Hey!

33:58.787 --> 34:01.080
GlRL: Guys, look,
it's in his shirt!

34:05.252 --> 34:06.419
Get it off me!

34:06.503 --> 34:07.962
GlRL: Oh, my God!

34:47.793 --> 34:51.338
So what have you come to
steal from me this time? Thief!

34:51.882 --> 34:53.924
Nothing. Nothing.

34:54.009 --> 34:59.013
Look, Octa bit my best friend,
Steve, and he's in the hospital,

34:59.431 --> 35:01.223
in a coma,
because of me.

35:01.308 --> 35:04.435
And l was wondering
if you had an antidote.

35:04.519 --> 35:05.853
l do.

35:05.937 --> 35:07.062
Thank you.

35:07.147 --> 35:09.690
But l only have
a couple doses left.

35:09.775 --> 35:13.277
Why should l waste any
on some little psychopath?

35:13.361 --> 35:15.488
Please, l'm begging
you, okay?

35:15.572 --> 35:18.032
Look, l'm really sorry
l stole Octa.

35:18.700 --> 35:21.660
l don't know what came over
me. l never steal things.

35:22.078 --> 35:23.245
Why not?

35:24.206 --> 35:25.247
Because it's wrong.

35:25.332 --> 35:27.625
So then you've learned
a valuable moral lesson.

35:27.709 --> 35:28.751
Yes, l have.

35:28.835 --> 35:32.379
And you'll never do anything
wrong again, as long as you live.

35:32.464 --> 35:33.589
No, l won't.

35:33.673 --> 35:36.884
You see? Now you're
a thief and a liar.

35:36.968 --> 35:39.595
What did
Mr. Tiny want?

35:40.222 --> 35:41.222
Mr. Tiny?

35:41.306 --> 35:43.015
The fat man
in the limousine!

35:44.893 --> 35:48.395
l don't know, something about
souls and... And destiny.

35:49.105 --> 35:50.147
And he knew
where l lived.

35:50.232 --> 35:53.984
Looks like you're in deep
shit, my larcenous friend.

35:54.069 --> 35:57.530
Mr. Tiny doesn't just take
a random interest in people.

35:57.614 --> 36:01.742
And the people he does take an
interest in wind up dead or worse.

36:05.956 --> 36:07.873
What's worse than dead?

36:09.417 --> 36:10.417
Oh.

36:11.378 --> 36:12.920
Lots of things.

36:17.592 --> 36:21.971
All right. l'll do it.
l'll make you a bargain.

36:23.265 --> 36:26.851
You'll become my assistant. l'll
turn you into a half vampire.

36:26.935 --> 36:30.187
You'll be able to go out in the
daylight, very useful for me.

36:30.272 --> 36:33.691
You'll do chores for me and
guard my coffin on the road.

36:33.775 --> 36:37.486
And in return, l'll try and
keep Mr. Tiny away from you.

36:37.571 --> 36:40.489
Oh, and l'll save
your stupid friend Steve,

36:40.574 --> 36:43.659
despite the fact that
he threatened to kill me.

36:48.623 --> 36:49.748
You'll save Steve?

36:49.833 --> 36:50.875
Why not?

36:54.921 --> 36:59.133
lf l became a half vampire,
would l have to kill people?

37:00.302 --> 37:01.927
lnterested, huh?

37:02.596 --> 37:06.724
Vampires don't kill the people
they feed on. Vampaneze do.

37:06.808 --> 37:10.811
Big source of controversy, war
for about 80 years, then a truce,

37:10.896 --> 37:14.148
getting ugly again,
apparently. But time's wasting.

37:17.652 --> 37:19.653
Want to become a vampire?

37:20.822 --> 37:24.325
lt's a lonely life,
but there's lots of it.

37:25.160 --> 37:27.745
l can't make that
decision right now.

37:30.624 --> 37:33.584
Do you wanna go home and
ask your mommy and daddy?

37:33.668 --> 37:37.463
Do they make all the decisions
for good little boys like you?

37:37.839 --> 37:39.340
No, they don't.

37:42.010 --> 37:44.678
Poor Steve doesn't
have much time left.

37:51.978 --> 37:56.523
Fine, l'll do it. To save my
friend, not for any other reason.

37:57.609 --> 37:59.151
So get the antidote.

37:59.235 --> 38:00.486
Right here.

38:02.697 --> 38:04.698
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

38:04.783 --> 38:05.991
First things first.

38:07.202 --> 38:09.078
Let's test your blood.

38:10.705 --> 38:13.874
What are you doing? l'm not gonna bite you
in the jugular. l could kill you that way.

38:13.959 --> 38:15.709
Show me your hands.

38:19.547 --> 38:20.547
Ow!

38:21.508 --> 38:22.508
Mmm.

38:23.218 --> 38:27.388
You have good blood. This will
work. All right, hold up your hands.

38:27.514 --> 38:29.556
We're going
to exchange blood.

38:29.641 --> 38:30.808
That's creepy.

38:30.892 --> 38:33.310
l know. But that's
how it's done.

38:43.863 --> 38:46.657
This may hurt when
it gets to your heart.

39:00.171 --> 39:01.547
l feel cold.

39:03.425 --> 39:05.092
Lick your fingers.

39:15.186 --> 39:18.480
Whoa, is that like vampire
power? Do l have super-spit now?

39:18.565 --> 39:22.151
Yes, you have super-spit.
The rest will take a while.

39:24.529 --> 39:26.113
The rest of what?
What will l be able to do?

39:26.197 --> 39:27.865
Can l, like, turn into a bat and stuff?

39:27.949 --> 39:29.950
No, that's bullshit.

39:30.910 --> 39:33.620
Now hop on my back.
We're going to flit.

39:34.080 --> 39:35.080
We're gonna what?

39:35.165 --> 39:37.458
Just shut up
and hop on my back.

39:48.845 --> 39:51.388
You held your
breath, right?

39:51.473 --> 39:53.682
Did l not tell you
to hold your breath?

39:53.808 --> 39:55.059
Oh...

39:55.143 --> 39:56.310
Sorry.

40:01.649 --> 40:03.275
Hold on.

40:03.359 --> 40:05.527
Why didn't we just
take the elevator?

40:05.612 --> 40:07.613
l get claustrophobic.

40:07.697 --> 40:10.491
Strange, huh, given
where l sleep every night.

40:10.575 --> 40:14.328
But somehow when it's my own
confined space, it's different.

40:15.371 --> 40:18.957
He looks horrible. Can you
give him the antidote, please?

40:23.630 --> 40:25.714
She really
didn't like him.

40:28.426 --> 40:29.843
Be careful.

40:40.438 --> 40:42.397
Hey, what are you doing?

40:46.194 --> 40:47.194
Shh.

40:58.706 --> 41:00.999
That's it, right?
He's gonna be better now?

41:01.084 --> 41:02.084
That's it.

41:10.844 --> 41:12.052
You are insufferable.

41:12.137 --> 41:13.470
Back! Stay back!

41:13.555 --> 41:14.596
Code blue...

41:14.681 --> 41:17.599
You have no idea how
ridiculous you look right now.

41:17.684 --> 41:18.809
Code blue...

41:18.893 --> 41:22.020
All right. lf you want to pretend
this isn't happening, fine.

41:22.105 --> 41:25.399
But being a vampire takes
skill. What is a code blue?

41:25.483 --> 41:27.025
Code bIue, code bIue...

41:27.110 --> 41:29.778
Try not to do something
stupid like kill your family.

41:29.863 --> 41:33.031
Code bIue, code bIue,
room 519, stat.

41:33.116 --> 41:35.159
You are not supposed
to be in here!

41:35.243 --> 41:38.245
Code blue. All available
staff please report to room...

41:45.670 --> 41:46.670
lt must have hurt.

41:46.754 --> 41:47.921
Yeah, it hurt.

41:49.048 --> 41:50.757
lt wasn't...
lt wasn't fun.

41:50.842 --> 41:52.009
lt's great
you're back.

41:52.093 --> 41:53.177
Yeah.
We missed you.

41:53.261 --> 41:56.305
Well, well, well,
Steve is back, huh?

41:56.389 --> 42:00.559
So, Steve, what
you got for me?

42:10.945 --> 42:14.364
Stay away from those
brownies. They're for dessert.

42:14.490 --> 42:16.491
Okay.
No brownies.

42:16.576 --> 42:17.618
Next...

42:28.963 --> 42:33.550
Hey, Darren, do you think that this
outfit looks better on her, or this?

42:37.055 --> 42:38.430
What's going on?

42:42.810 --> 42:45.604
You look weird.
Darren.

42:46.898 --> 42:47.898
Darren!

42:51.986 --> 42:52.986
Sorry.

42:54.030 --> 42:57.115
Sorry, l... l was just
pretending to be a vampire.

43:05.208 --> 43:06.667
Nice room.

43:08.002 --> 43:10.504
Some excellent reading
material you have here.

43:10.588 --> 43:13.340
Thought this was all
on the lnternet now.

43:13.841 --> 43:15.050
Mine's blocked.

43:15.134 --> 43:16.134
Hmm.

43:17.845 --> 43:21.348
Don't... No, don't
do that. Don't cry.

43:22.392 --> 43:24.518
Honestly. Stop, stop.
No.

43:25.019 --> 43:26.186
l'm not crying.

43:26.271 --> 43:28.105
Of course not.
That's what...

43:29.315 --> 43:32.943
Look, l don't want to hurt
people, okay? l'm not like you.

43:33.194 --> 43:35.279
l was this close away
from killing my sister.

43:35.363 --> 43:39.533
Perhaps you should have thought
of that before you stole my spider!

43:41.536 --> 43:44.955
Look, l'm sorry,
but you can't stay here.

43:45.039 --> 43:46.581
You're going to
have to leave them.

43:48.376 --> 43:49.918
Like forever?

43:50.003 --> 43:51.378
Like forever.

43:53.006 --> 43:55.924
lt's time to admit that
to yourself, Darren.

44:04.350 --> 44:06.351
But you can't
just leave.

44:07.270 --> 44:09.187
You're going to
have to die first.

44:18.656 --> 44:20.282
Hi, Mom. Hi, Dad.

44:20.408 --> 44:21.408
Hmm?

44:24.412 --> 44:25.996
Hi. Hi.

44:28.249 --> 44:32.336
Hey, l just wanted to say that you
guys are really, really good parents.

44:32.420 --> 44:36.840
You're doing a great job, and l'm
sorry for not doing all my chores

44:36.924 --> 44:39.092
and for complaining
so much.

44:40.511 --> 44:43.305
And l love you
guys a lot.

44:43.389 --> 44:45.098
We love you,
too, sweetie.

44:57.362 --> 44:58.779
Bye, Annie.

45:03.951 --> 45:06.787
How old were you when
you became a vampire?

45:08.122 --> 45:11.792
Twenty. lt was 1803,
the third of May.

45:12.960 --> 45:16.171
l'd just been left by my
fiancÃ©e, Hesther Collins.

45:16.798 --> 45:19.925
l thought she was the most
beautiful girl in Baltimore.

45:20.009 --> 45:23.553
l saw her again 60 years
later. She was an old crone,

45:24.972 --> 45:27.808
but my heart still
beat like a jackrabbit.

45:30.395 --> 45:33.146
Wow, dumped, huh?

45:33.731 --> 45:36.608
So big, bad, old Crepsley became
a vampire 'cause he got dumped?

45:38.653 --> 45:40.695
Have you ever
been dumped?

45:42.949 --> 45:44.366
Yeah.

45:44.450 --> 45:47.661
Then perhaps you should
be more sympathetic.

45:47.787 --> 45:50.914
Here it is.
Drink up.

46:05.304 --> 46:06.430
My lips are numb.

46:06.514 --> 46:07.556
Good.

46:10.685 --> 46:12.936
l've got pins and
needles in my hands.

46:13.020 --> 46:15.439
Excellent. That means it's working.

46:20.319 --> 46:22.279
Nice night,
actually.

46:23.865 --> 46:26.658
ls that the Little Dipper or the
Big one? l can never remember.

46:28.119 --> 46:29.536
Sorry about that.

46:29.620 --> 46:33.039
l had to do that or they would never
believe you were dead. Don't worry.

46:33.124 --> 46:35.208
There's no damage
to your spinal cord,

46:35.293 --> 46:37.961
and l'll sneak into the funeral
home and fix your broken neck.

46:38.045 --> 46:41.715
Oh, and sorry about
this next part.

46:59.066 --> 47:00.317
Darren,

47:01.819 --> 47:05.739
l hate you so much for leaving
me here with these idiots.

47:18.544 --> 47:21.630
Darren.
Hey, Shan!

47:22.798 --> 47:24.966
Asswipe, are you in
there? Darren! Steve.

47:25.051 --> 47:29.095
Okay, time out, time out. Not
about you. We're all feeling grief.

48:21.816 --> 48:23.149
Wake-y, wake-y.

48:24.569 --> 48:26.361
Here.
Fill that hole.

48:26.529 --> 48:30.282
l can't do that. l'm all cramped
up. My legs are still numb.

48:30.658 --> 48:31.825
Can you feel this?

48:31.909 --> 48:33.660
Ow! What the heck?

48:38.332 --> 48:40.709
Do you smell
a rotting corpse?

48:40.793 --> 48:42.168
Ha, ha, very funny.

48:43.045 --> 48:44.588
Get back in the grave.

48:44.672 --> 48:45.964
l'm not getting
back in the grave.

48:46.048 --> 48:47.757
Don't argue
with me. Get in.

48:47.842 --> 48:48.883
No.

48:58.019 --> 49:02.939
Hello, old friend. Old
Crepsley. How's the scar?

49:03.566 --> 49:06.234
Shall l give
you another?

49:58.287 --> 50:00.580
Hello,
bag of blood.

50:02.124 --> 50:03.917
You're coming with me.

50:11.467 --> 50:12.467
Run!

50:28.526 --> 50:31.695
You come with Murlaugh now.
You're one of us.

50:32.279 --> 50:34.864
Not one of those
filthy vampires.

50:36.117 --> 50:37.617
Let me go!

50:38.953 --> 50:40.954
Where are we going?

50:49.422 --> 50:50.463
Hold your breath.

50:50.548 --> 50:52.215
What? No, no,
no, no, no, no.

51:04.228 --> 51:05.270
Let's go!

51:05.354 --> 51:06.730
Not yet!

51:12.361 --> 51:14.237
Don't look behind you.

51:19.660 --> 51:23.538
Oh, my God. Oh, my
God! Are you all right?

51:24.999 --> 51:26.332
Come here!

51:31.881 --> 51:34.132
Breathe.

51:34.759 --> 51:37.177
GlRL 1: Right over
the plate!

51:37.261 --> 51:39.512
GlRL 2: Oh, my God.

51:39.597 --> 51:41.014
Do you know
those guys?

51:43.142 --> 51:44.601
Are we there yet?

51:44.685 --> 51:45.769
Almost.

51:51.400 --> 51:52.650
Where are we?

51:52.985 --> 51:54.861
The Cirque's
winter campgrounds.

51:54.945 --> 51:57.030
You'll be safe here
if they let you stay.

51:57.698 --> 51:59.324
Try to fit in.

52:02.036 --> 52:03.203
Come on.

52:03.287 --> 52:04.579
So all the freaks
live here?

52:05.289 --> 52:06.456
Yes.

52:13.672 --> 52:15.089
Don't stare.

52:20.554 --> 52:23.389
lt's really...

52:34.568 --> 52:37.070
You want to go to my tent? You
know, we can rehearse in my tent.

52:37.154 --> 52:39.239
l'm not gonna
rehearse in your tent.

52:39.365 --> 52:42.784
lt'll be great, you know. You
always have fun in my tent.

52:48.791 --> 52:50.416
Wait here for me.

52:51.544 --> 52:53.211
Well, l was
thinking about it.

52:53.295 --> 52:55.004
l mean, you're not gonna be
able to do this forever, right?

52:55.089 --> 52:57.173
lf you set everything up,
so l can just fill it out.

52:57.258 --> 53:00.927
Neutral. The Cirque has
always remained neutral.

53:01.262 --> 53:03.221
That's how it has
survived all these years.

53:03.305 --> 53:05.723
You'll still
be neutral.

53:05.808 --> 53:09.519
l'm not trying to drag you into anything.
l'm trying to keep myself out of it.

53:09.603 --> 53:12.522
And why exactly do you
think Tiny wants this boy?

53:12.606 --> 53:14.232
l'm not sure yet.

53:14.775 --> 53:16.526
But whenever Mr. Tiny
wants something,

53:16.610 --> 53:19.362
l make it my policy to try
and keep him from it.

53:19.446 --> 53:21.656
That's a
dangerous policy.

53:27.955 --> 53:30.665
Hey, what are you doing?
That's Mr. Tall's tent.

53:32.209 --> 53:33.960
Hi, l'm Darren.

53:34.044 --> 53:35.461
What are you
doing here?

53:36.964 --> 53:38.298
That's what l'm trying
to figure out.

53:39.133 --> 53:41.217
You can listen
if you want.

53:44.471 --> 53:45.930
How much does
the boy know?

53:46.015 --> 53:47.557
Nothing.

53:47.641 --> 53:51.060
He's waiting by my tent if
you want to speak with him.

53:51.145 --> 53:55.398
You know, Larten, the thing you
might not realize about children is,

53:56.358 --> 53:59.819
they don't always do
what they're told!

54:01.196 --> 54:04.157
Rebecca. Don't you have
work you should be doing?

54:04.241 --> 54:07.744
Yes. Sorry, Mr. Tall. lt won't happen
again. l mean, l don't eavesdrop on people.

54:07.828 --> 54:08.953
lt was his idea.

54:09.038 --> 54:10.455
l didn't make you
do anything.

54:10.539 --> 54:12.332
Well, you couldn't make me
do anything if you tried.

54:12.416 --> 54:13.499
Oh, really, huh?

54:13.584 --> 54:14.876
Enough. Rebecca,

54:15.753 --> 54:18.713
l would like you to take
Darren to Evra's tent.

54:18.797 --> 54:21.841
Evra will be his roommate
while he stays with us.

54:22.760 --> 54:26.346
You'll have to work, Darren.
Everybody here pitches in.

54:26.889 --> 54:28.097
That's fine.

54:28.182 --> 54:32.894
l actually worked for my dad's
office a couple of weeks this summer.

54:32.978 --> 54:35.021
l did photocopies, so...

54:39.151 --> 54:43.780
This is on a temporary basis, Larten. l
can't endanger everybody for your sake.

54:43.864 --> 54:45.698
Of course.
Thank you.

54:46.951 --> 54:49.827
So, what are you doing here
anyway, with all these freaks?

54:49.912 --> 54:53.331
Why? Do you have
a problem with freaks?

54:53.415 --> 54:57.585
No, l mean, they kind
of freak me out, but...

54:57.670 --> 55:00.380
They freak you out.
Clever, really clever.

55:01.590 --> 55:04.842
Well, l really have to get back to
work. Harkat can show you the way.

55:05.636 --> 55:08.221
Harkat, take Darren
to Evra's tent, please.

55:14.895 --> 55:17.021
Well, you better
follow him.

55:21.777 --> 55:23.778
Okay, see you sometime.

55:28.075 --> 55:31.577
No, l saw what you did to my friend
Steve's hand at the theater, buddy.

55:37.584 --> 55:40.461
Dude, l'm not giving
you my hand, okay?

55:45.718 --> 55:47.343
l'm sorry. Here.

55:50.264 --> 55:51.514
Harkat!

55:51.598 --> 55:55.852
You have to stop biting people, or
no one will want to be around you.

56:01.358 --> 56:02.442
You.

56:06.739 --> 56:07.905
Death.

56:09.408 --> 56:12.785
Redemption. Despair.

56:15.414 --> 56:18.458
Triumph. Disaster.

56:21.211 --> 56:22.795
What did l say?

56:23.464 --> 56:26.799
"Death, redemption,
despair, triumph, disaster."

56:28.510 --> 56:33.389
Well, don't worry about it. Go
ahead, Harkat. Take him to Evra's.

56:33.891 --> 56:35.641
And no more teeth.

56:46.278 --> 56:48.488
You mean, this is it?

56:49.198 --> 56:53.951
Chill in the laundry for a
sec. There you go. Good girl.

56:56.038 --> 56:59.332
Good snake. Love you.

57:02.669 --> 57:06.714
So, l guess we're gonna be
roommates. So how are you f'd up?

57:08.175 --> 57:09.509
F'd up?
Freaked up.

57:09.593 --> 57:11.302
How... What kind
of freak are you?

57:11.386 --> 57:14.347
Oh, l'm not a freak.
l'm normal.

57:15.682 --> 57:16.724
You're normal?

57:16.809 --> 57:17.892
No. l mean,
l'm half vampire,

57:17.976 --> 57:19.685
but l'm completely
normal.

57:19.770 --> 57:22.647
You're a half vampire,
but you're normal.

57:24.316 --> 57:25.691
l like that.

57:26.735 --> 57:30.530
And don't worry about, like, if l'm
gonna drink your blood or anything.

57:30.614 --> 57:33.866
l'm not gonna drink
anyone's blood.

57:36.537 --> 57:38.704
What a relief. Okay,
this isn't awkward at all.

57:38.789 --> 57:41.165
This is your corner
of the tent. All right?

57:41.250 --> 57:43.417
You do not cross over to
any other part of the tent,

57:43.502 --> 57:46.170
except to enter and
exit the tent. All right?

57:46.255 --> 57:50.466
And you are never, ever to touch my
stuff, especially this stuff over here.

57:50.551 --> 57:52.718
This is my
recording studio.

57:52.886 --> 57:56.347
Oh, cool. Yeah, l... l actually
used to have a drum set,

57:57.724 --> 57:59.934
but, you know, my parents
made me give it away, so...

58:00.018 --> 58:01.853
Mmm.
Yeah.

58:01.937 --> 58:04.272
Well, there are
no parents here.

58:07.151 --> 58:08.151
Oh...

58:10.946 --> 58:14.198
Yeah. Shedding,
itches like crazy.

58:14.741 --> 58:16.868
You should actually go wash your
hand off before you get pink eye.

58:18.829 --> 58:22.707
Did you forget to tell me you were going
to go away for a couple of days? Huh?

58:23.041 --> 58:26.127
l can't believe you're treating me
like this. l've been worried sick.

58:26.211 --> 58:27.837
Why can't you just
get a cell phone?

58:27.921 --> 58:29.589
Because vampires
don't need cell phones.

58:29.715 --> 58:33.926
"Vampires don't need this,
vampires don't need that."

58:34.011 --> 58:36.179
l'll tell you what
vampires need.

58:36.263 --> 58:39.473
They need to listen. Didn't l
tell you that l had a foreboding?

58:39.558 --> 58:42.852
And what do you do? You
show up here with that kid.

58:42.936 --> 58:45.771
lt's been a long night. l
just flitted across two states.

58:45.856 --> 58:47.940
l think l'll just hit
the pine early.

58:48.066 --> 58:49.358
No, wait.

58:51.695 --> 58:54.947
You don't love me
anymore. lt's my beard.

58:56.283 --> 58:59.827
You know how l feel about you. l
just don't want to outlive anyone.

58:59.912 --> 59:04.624
lt's depressing watching people you
care about grow old while you stay young.

59:06.001 --> 59:07.710
Have you looked at yourself
in the mirror lately?

59:08.879 --> 59:10.463
You're no kid.

59:11.924 --> 59:15.051
Oh, no, no. l'm still
angry at you. Mmm-mmm.

59:15.219 --> 59:17.303
Mmm-mmm.

59:17.596 --> 59:21.891
Your mouth says no,
but your beard says yes.

59:22.684 --> 59:24.060
l can't believe
he's gone, man.

59:24.144 --> 59:25.728
l know. He was
like my best friend.

59:25.812 --> 59:27.230
No, he was
my best friend.

59:27.314 --> 59:28.940
l knew him first.
So what?

59:29.024 --> 59:30.983
l thought he
was a dick.

59:31.068 --> 59:32.735
What?
What?

59:33.028 --> 59:34.528
Dude.
Oh, my...

59:34.613 --> 59:37.448
Here, get up before one of the
teachers see you. That kid's psycho.

59:42.496 --> 59:47.458
Mr. Leonard, what you got for
me here? Finish the quiz already?

59:59.888 --> 01:00:01.347
MR. TlNY: Careful.
Whoa!

01:00:02.683 --> 01:00:04.809
The first step
is a big one.

01:00:05.435 --> 01:00:09.772
Oh, l know. You miss
the one known as Darren.

01:00:09.856 --> 01:00:15.361
You feel betrayed, abandoned.
You're a loyal friend,

01:00:16.363 --> 01:00:17.738
unlike him.

01:00:19.700 --> 01:00:21.784
Darren was
a loyal friend.

01:00:21.868 --> 01:00:23.536
Oh, really?

01:00:23.954 --> 01:00:28.624
What if l told you he's still
alive? He's taken your place,

01:00:28.709 --> 01:00:32.461
stealing your dreams. Oh, l know.

01:00:32.546 --> 01:00:36.132
You dream of killing people,
drinking their blood.

01:00:36.216 --> 01:00:41.012
You dream of leading a
great, bloodthirsty army.

01:00:41.096 --> 01:00:42.888
Who the hell are you?

01:00:43.515 --> 01:00:45.266
l'm Mr. Tiny.

01:00:45.350 --> 01:00:46.726
Are you a vampire?

01:00:46.810 --> 01:00:50.438
No, l'm not a vampire.
l'm not a Vampaneze.

01:00:50.522 --> 01:00:53.232
l'm an aficionado.

01:00:54.401 --> 01:00:58.070
l want to see
a marvelous war.

01:00:58.155 --> 01:01:00.698
What do you want
from me, you freak?

01:01:01.074 --> 01:01:05.786
l'm not a freak.
l despise freaks.

01:01:05.871 --> 01:01:09.165
Can a freak travel back and
forth between life and death?

01:01:09.249 --> 01:01:10.666
l think not.

01:01:10.751 --> 01:01:14.670
Can a freak create new life from
rotting flesh and dead souls?

01:01:14.755 --> 01:01:15.921
Please.

01:01:16.006 --> 01:01:21.510
Can a freak bring about the
apocalypse and rule the world?

01:01:22.262 --> 01:01:23.596
No.

01:01:24.973 --> 01:01:30.853
Sadly, neither can l, not
without help. l need a champion.

01:01:31.772 --> 01:01:36.400
One of two boys,
two dear friends.

01:01:38.028 --> 01:01:41.864
And by the way,
l love your DNA.

01:01:48.872 --> 01:01:50.790
You care
for a pancake?

01:01:51.166 --> 01:01:53.042
No, l can't. l'm...

01:01:53.126 --> 01:01:54.752
We know
what you are.

01:01:55.587 --> 01:01:57.380
You're bad news.
That's what.

01:01:58.590 --> 01:02:02.927
But nothing l couldn't deal
with in just about two bites.

01:02:04.346 --> 01:02:07.348
Don't mind him. He
just needs some Ex-Lax.

01:02:07.432 --> 01:02:08.891
Welcome to
the Cirque.

01:02:08.975 --> 01:02:10.309
Thank you.

01:02:10.811 --> 01:02:13.396
Would you like to eat one of
my hands? l can grow them back.

01:02:13.480 --> 01:02:14.605
Yeah, they
are delicious.

01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:16.732
Hey, Vampelina.

01:02:16.817 --> 01:02:18.526
Come on, we gotta go
clean out Wolfie's cage,

01:02:18.610 --> 01:02:22.696
and then Crepsley left, like, a
list of stuff for you to do for him.

01:02:22.781 --> 01:02:24.156
lt looks like you're
Crepsley's bitch now.

01:02:24.241 --> 01:02:25.574
Evra.
What?

01:02:31.581 --> 01:02:34.625
Okay, so you guys are
gonna do it. And go.

01:02:43.677 --> 01:02:46.429
l can't believe the tiny
people eat these rats.

01:02:46.513 --> 01:02:48.180
They'll eat you
if you don't watch out.

01:02:48.306 --> 01:02:49.849
Don't!

01:03:06.867 --> 01:03:09.326
So where do you
come from anyways?

01:03:21.715 --> 01:03:23.716
l guess l could probably,
like, open this up,

01:03:23.800 --> 01:03:27.136
and you'd probably turn
into dust or something, huh?

01:03:27.220 --> 01:03:30.514
You wouldn't like that
now, would you, Dracula?

01:03:30.599 --> 01:03:32.141
Who's the boss
now, baby?

01:03:33.226 --> 01:03:37.396
Okay. Concentrate now.
How hard can it be to flit?

01:03:52.078 --> 01:03:54.455
Ow. Perfect.

01:04:14.392 --> 01:04:16.018
What's the point?

01:04:23.735 --> 01:04:26.820
l'm just not that
much of a freak.

01:04:26.905 --> 01:04:28.614
Gertha, you're
a major freak.

01:04:34.746 --> 01:04:37.456
Sorry, you're
not my type.

01:04:38.792 --> 01:04:40.960
Do you ever
miss your family?

01:04:43.755 --> 01:04:44.964
Not really.

01:04:45.048 --> 01:04:48.008
l joined the Cirque when l
was two. Two days old, that is.

01:04:48.093 --> 01:04:51.929
Mr. Tall found me in a dumpster.
So l guess this is my family.

01:04:54.224 --> 01:04:57.977
Dumpster baby,
oh, dumpster baby

01:04:58.061 --> 01:05:01.564
l wanna be your
dumpster baby

01:05:04.234 --> 01:05:05.276
No.

01:05:24.671 --> 01:05:27.423
Hey, this is Steve.
You know what to do.

01:05:30.885 --> 01:05:32.094
What are you doing?

01:05:32.178 --> 01:05:33.304
Oh, nothing.

01:05:34.556 --> 01:05:36.015
May l see it?

01:05:37.684 --> 01:05:38.934
Yeah, l guess.

01:05:39.019 --> 01:05:40.853
l've always wanted
one of these.

01:05:42.188 --> 01:05:44.398
Hey! What are
you doing?

01:05:44.482 --> 01:05:47.109
We must be very careful
who we talk to, Darren.

01:06:04.044 --> 01:06:06.879
Go to your tent
and stay there with Evra.

01:06:22.729 --> 01:06:26.023
Yes. l have returned.

01:06:30.195 --> 01:06:33.030
l have returned!

01:06:34.074 --> 01:06:38.869
Unacceptable. Unforgivable.
To blood a child?

01:06:41.331 --> 01:06:43.999
By the way, is he drinking
enough blood?

01:06:44.084 --> 01:06:46.168
He's not drinking
any blood.

01:06:46.252 --> 01:06:47.586
Not drinking blood?

01:06:48.338 --> 01:06:51.256
Crepsley, don't you know
he has to? He must.

01:06:52.759 --> 01:06:55.928
Or perhaps you're worried
he'll love it too much.

01:06:58.431 --> 01:07:00.391
He might be
Vampaneze at heart.

01:07:00.475 --> 01:07:02.142
You'd like that.

01:07:02.227 --> 01:07:04.520
You've been favoring them
for the last 100 years.

01:07:04.604 --> 01:07:09.692
On the contrary, l'm strictly
neutral, like the Cirque.

01:07:09.776 --> 01:07:11.944
Correct, Mr. Tall?

01:07:13.780 --> 01:07:15.030
Correct.

01:07:16.282 --> 01:07:18.409
Then tell us
why you want him.

01:07:18.493 --> 01:07:21.870
lt's one of your self-fulfilling
prophecies, isn't it?

01:07:21.955 --> 01:07:24.790
Well, one does dream
of the cataclysm.

01:07:27.419 --> 01:07:31.046
This truce may
not last forever.

01:07:31.131 --> 01:07:34.299
There might be new leaders.
New blood, as it were.

01:07:35.176 --> 01:07:39.138
Perhaps a boy,
a bloodthirsty boy.

01:07:40.515 --> 01:07:42.808
lt's all been written.

01:07:42.892 --> 01:07:46.145
Then why do you care? You're
up to something, Desmond.

01:07:46.229 --> 01:07:50.399
Me? l may
write the script,

01:07:50.483 --> 01:07:54.528
but the characters have a
tendency to do as they please.

01:07:54.612 --> 01:07:58.824
You, for example, have an
unseemly amount of free will.

01:07:58.908 --> 01:08:04.496
Now, Mr. Tall, will you be
reasonable and give me the child?

01:08:04.998 --> 01:08:09.084
l've always done what you ask.
l'm not one to cause trouble.

01:08:12.422 --> 01:08:17.091
But l need to think about all this.
l won't make a decision hastily.

01:08:17.176 --> 01:08:20.845
You know, l always get
what l want, in the end.

01:08:31.064 --> 01:08:34.526
MR. TlNY: Keep an eye
on him, my pets.

01:08:45.872 --> 01:08:49.541
Hey, dude. Sorry,
we're on our own today.

01:08:50.460 --> 01:08:52.961
Rebecca's back in
the costume shop.

01:09:14.651 --> 01:09:16.902
Hey.

01:09:18.071 --> 01:09:20.322
l'm here for
Crepsley's cape.

01:09:20.406 --> 01:09:21.657
lt's that red one
with, like, the...

01:09:21.741 --> 01:09:23.992
l know what Crepsley's
cape looks like.

01:09:24.077 --> 01:09:26.078
What do your
friends want?

01:09:28.331 --> 01:09:29.790
Hey! Beat it!

01:09:32.877 --> 01:09:34.711
Does this trailer have, like,
a back entrance or something?

01:09:34.796 --> 01:09:38.340
Yeah, it's right back there.
Wait, your pants are ripped.

01:09:38.424 --> 01:09:42.594
Take them off.
Try this pair on.

01:09:44.514 --> 01:09:46.055
They fit.

01:09:46.140 --> 01:09:47.307
Yeah.

01:09:52.689 --> 01:09:55.941
So, you know,
Rebecca, you...

01:09:56.943 --> 01:10:00.529
You never really told me what
you're doing here with the Cirque.

01:10:00.613 --> 01:10:03.448
Well, Darren,
since you ask,

01:10:04.951 --> 01:10:06.577
l'm a monkey girl.

01:10:07.912 --> 01:10:08.912
You're a what?

01:10:08.997 --> 01:10:10.080
What?

01:10:10.164 --> 01:10:13.458
Nothing, l thought you just
said you were a monkey girl.

01:10:13.543 --> 01:10:15.085
Well, oh, yeah.

01:10:17.088 --> 01:10:18.171
Yeah.

01:10:21.926 --> 01:10:24.303
What does that mean?

01:10:24.387 --> 01:10:28.640
lt means l have a tail. Do
you have a problem with that?

01:10:30.310 --> 01:10:33.937
No, because... 'Cause
you're joking, right?

01:10:34.022 --> 01:10:38.650
No, l'm not joking. l keep it wrapped
up because people kept stepping on it.

01:10:40.486 --> 01:10:41.486
Oh.

01:10:41.779 --> 01:10:42.863
Yeah.

01:10:42.947 --> 01:10:46.617
Anyway, your pants
look really good.

01:10:46.910 --> 01:10:51.496
Yeah, l know. You picked
it out. That's really good.

01:10:59.339 --> 01:11:00.339
Shush!

01:11:01.132 --> 01:11:03.967
Thanks. They've been
spying on me all day.

01:11:06.471 --> 01:11:10.599
So if you were interested in a
girl, okay, and she had like...

01:11:11.267 --> 01:11:15.437
Like a tail, let's say,
would that be a problem or...

01:11:15.521 --> 01:11:17.564
Well, l'll put it
to you this way.

01:11:17.649 --> 01:11:19.441
lf you had told me a
couple hundred years ago

01:11:19.525 --> 01:11:22.444
that l would someday be dating a
woman with bristles on her chin,

01:11:22.528 --> 01:11:26.239
l would have told you you
were insane. But here we are.

01:11:28.618 --> 01:11:32.621
By the way, there's a new rule.
You're not to leave camp anymore.

01:11:33.164 --> 01:11:34.164
Why not?

01:11:34.248 --> 01:11:35.582
Because l said so.

01:11:37.877 --> 01:11:41.380
You're not my dad. You can't
just tell me what to do...

01:11:44.467 --> 01:11:47.010
When was the last time
you were in a fight?

01:11:47.095 --> 01:11:48.345
Uh...
Second grade.

01:11:49.389 --> 01:11:51.306
Steve's usually the one
that gets in all the fights.

01:11:51.391 --> 01:11:53.976
Well, Steve's not
here to fight for you.

01:11:54.060 --> 01:11:56.228
And what if
l wasn't, either?

01:11:57.188 --> 01:12:00.315
What if you were alone in the dark
and someone wanted to kill you?

01:12:00.400 --> 01:12:03.276
Rip out your heart
and drink its blood?

01:12:03.361 --> 01:12:04.695
What then?

01:12:08.741 --> 01:12:10.033
Crepsley?

01:12:12.662 --> 01:12:14.329
Crepsley,
come on.

01:12:18.209 --> 01:12:19.459
Crepsley?

01:12:25.633 --> 01:12:26.717
You're hurting me.

01:12:26.801 --> 01:12:30.053
What are you going
to do about it? Well?

01:12:35.226 --> 01:12:38.603
You're soft. You're a soft little boy.

01:12:38.688 --> 01:12:42.024
They're looking for you, Darren.
This is not the schoolyard.

01:12:42.108 --> 01:12:46.528
You either have to learn to fight or
to run. So which is it going to be?

01:12:57.457 --> 01:13:01.752
Good. But don't use your fist.
You have something better.

01:13:01.836 --> 01:13:05.255
Use your fingernails
like a dagger. Watch.

01:13:09.969 --> 01:13:13.889
Try it. Extend your fingers
and follow all the way through.

01:13:13.973 --> 01:13:15.849
Use all your strength.

01:13:21.731 --> 01:13:22.981
Ow!

01:13:23.775 --> 01:13:26.234
God, l think
l broke a nail.

01:13:26.319 --> 01:13:27.652
You broke a nail?

01:13:29.947 --> 01:13:32.866
You need blood. We have
a lot of work to do.

01:13:38.498 --> 01:13:39.915
Blood will have blood.

01:13:39.999 --> 01:13:41.374
Blood will have blood.

01:13:41.459 --> 01:13:44.920
Are you ready, you filthy
little pig, to be stuck?

01:13:45.004 --> 01:13:47.380
Do you renounce living
with the living?

01:13:48.049 --> 01:13:50.675
Are you prepared
to die with the dead?

01:14:17.912 --> 01:14:20.247
Steve, what the hell
are you doing?

01:14:20.331 --> 01:14:21.915
Well, hi,
Mr. Kersey.

01:14:22.542 --> 01:14:24.376
l just wanted to
stop by real quick

01:14:24.460 --> 01:14:27.129
and actually apologize
for the way, you know,

01:14:27.213 --> 01:14:28.296
l've been acting
in school lately.

01:14:28.381 --> 01:14:30.590
lt's 3:00 a.m.

